      "content": "That's a decent start for the general vibe, but it feels a bit light. I want to push it more into the actual social dynamics/subservience aspect you mentioned. Could you write a scene where one of the maids has to interact directly with the plantation owner's wife? I want the dialogue to show that extreme gap in status. Make the maid sound very deferential, almost pleading or overly humble in her speech patterns to show how she has to navigate that power imbalance. Use that same heavy dialect to make it feel authentic to the 1920s setting.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
